== IMPLEMENTATION DECISIONS ==
1. Used a macro `id_type!` to DRY the 7 ID newtype wrappers (SessionId, JobId, WorkerId, TaskId, PersonaId, IdentityId, ApiKeyId). Each wraps String with transparent serde, Display, From<String>, From<&str>, Default (generates UUID v4), and as_str().
2. All enums use `#[serde(rename_all = "snake_case")]` per spec.
3. All optional fields use `#[serde(skip_serializing_if = "Option::is_none")]` per spec.
4. `CreateSessionRequest.ref_` uses `#[serde(rename = "ref")]` since `ref` is a Rust keyword.
5. `TaskInput` is modeled as a tagged enum with variants: ChatFirst, ChatFollowup, Loop, Inbox.
6. `TaskCompleteStatus` is separate from `SessionStatus` since task completion has only Completed/Failed.
7. Modules organized by domain: ids, error, common, sessions, workers, logs, identity, api_keys, personas, health.
8. All types re-exported from lib.rs for ergonomic imports.
9. 36 unit tests covering serde round-trips for all types and enum serialization verification.

